Four people have been rescued from kidnappers following a gun duel with police at the Gwagwalada area of Abuja. According to the police, the victims are Umaru Salihu, Mariam Umaru, who were kidnapped from their home in Pagada village on February 8 at about 1am; Zilkifilu Usman and Usman Shuaibu, who were abducted from Niger State on February 2, while on transit. The FCT Police Public Relations Officer, Anjuguri Manzah, said that the four victims were successfully rescued from a hideout located at Sauni Hills, Lambata, at the FCT-Niger State boundary.